---
import DocsLayout from '@/layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
---

<DocsLayout title="Local History" description="Scrapeman captures every sent request in a compressed, template-preserving local history so secrets never touch disk." section="Local History">
  <h2>Overview</h2>
  <p>
    Every sent request is captured to a per-workspace JSONL file under the app data directory (never the workspace
    folder).
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Template-preserving</strong> — <code>{"{{token}}"}</code> stays as <code>{"{{token}}"}</code> on disk.
      Secrets are never baked into history.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Compressed</strong> — body preview fields are gzipped on disk when 256 bytes or larger (5–10x
      smaller).
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>History panel</h2>
  <p>The sidebar History panel shows recent requests with:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Method badge (<code>GET</code> / <code>POST</code> / <code>PUT</code> / etc.)</li>
    <li>Status pill (200 green, 4xx red, etc.)</li>
    <li>Relative time ("2 min ago")</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Click any entry to restore it into a new tab. Duplicate restores are detected and skipped.
  </p>

  <h2>Search and filter</h2>
  <p>
    The history panel has a search bar that filters by request name and URL.
  </p>
</DocsLayout>
